Definition: gruesomely indicative of death or the dead
Example: a charnel smell came from the chest filled with dead men's bones; ghastly shrieks; the sepulchral darkness of the catacombs
Synonyms: ghastly, noun, attribute, ghastliness, sepulchral, gruesomely, indicative, of, death, or, the, dead, a, smell, came, from, chest, filled, with, men, s, bones, shrieks, darkness, catacombs
Category: adj.all
